HEADWORD: Duotype
<hw>Du"o*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>duo</ets>
two + <ets>type</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Photoengraving)</fld> <def>A print
made from two half-tone plates made from the same negative, but etched
differently.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

